# CAWS-SESSION-LOG-RELOCATE-001 — packaging exclusion.
#
# The published tarball MUST NOT ship stray session-log / scratch content
# from the hook pack's tmp/ scratch directory. Before this slice, the
# claude-code hook pack wrote per-session turn logs + session-envelope
# state into `templates/hook-packs/claude-code/tmp/<session-id>/`. The
# package.json `files` field ships `templates/hook-packs/**`, and npm's
# `files` inclusion does NOT honor .gitignore — so those local session
# dirs leaked into the published package (27 files in one observed pack).
#
# Per-session state now lives in the CONSUMER's `.caws/sessions/` at
# runtime; the hook pack itself ships no tmp/ content.
#
# IMPORTANT (CAWS-SESSION-LOG-PACK-LEAK-HOTFIX-001): this `.npmignore` is
# DEFENSE-IN-DEPTH ONLY, not the operative guard. When a `files` field is
# present in package.json, npm's `files` inclusion takes PRECEDENCE over
# .npmignore for any path a `files` glob matches — so this exclusion alone
# does NOT drop the tmp/ files from the tarball (verified: 27 stray files
# still shipped with only this .npmignore). The OPERATIVE guard is the
# negation entry in package.json `files`:
#   "!templates/hook-packs/claude-code/tmp"
#   "!templates/hook-packs/claude-code/tmp/**"
# which npm honors. This file is kept for any future case where files-field
# precedence does not apply (e.g. a non-files-matched path).
templates/hook-packs/claude-code/tmp/
templates/hook-packs/claude-code/tmp/**
